  "response": "Hoei Shin, also known as H\u014dei Shin, was a Japanese monk who lived during the late 18th century and is notable for his contributions to the early development of Zen Buddhism in Japan. He is particularly remembered for his role in the transmission of Zen teachings and for his efforts to reform certain practices within the Zen Buddhist community.\n\nHis life and works reflect a significant period in the history of Japanese Buddhism when the religion was navigating the complexities of modernity and cultural change. However, detailed information about him is relatively scarce compared to more prominent historical figures in Japanese Buddhism.\n\nIf you are seeking specific information about a certain aspect of his life or teachings, please feel free to ask!",
